<script >
import MyColor from './MyColor.vue'

export default {
    components: { MyColor },
    data() {
        return {
            color1: '#3a86ff',
            color2: 'rgba(228, 193, 249, 0.79)'
        }
    }
}
</script>

<template>
    <h1 style="text-align: center;">JavaScript 系列九：第7課 ── 學習開發狀態複雜的 vue 元件</h1>
    <p><a href="https://rgbacolorpicker.com/rgba-to-hex" target="_blank">RGBA->HEX Convert check</a></p>
    <p><a href="https://rgbacolorpicker.com/hex-to-rgba" target="_blank">HEX->RGBA Convert check</a></p>
    <p>ps: the link tool hex to rgba provides only 2 digits decimal, but my covert tool is 3 digits decimal.</p>
    <p>
    <h2>Usage:</h2>
    <p>1. type hex code or RGBA code or each value of rgba next to the scroll bar or scroll the scroll bar.</p>
    <p>2. if you type in RGBA and each color is over 255 (over 1 for alpha), it will automatically return 255 (return 1 for
        alpha).</p>
    <p>3. click the button next to the hex / rgba code to copy the color version you like.</p>
    <p>ps: if there's no the last two digits which means alpha in hex code, it will regard as "FF", and it means alpha = 1
        in RGBA.</p>
    <p>ps: if no v-model in parent conponent (like the third demo), the default color is #000000FF.</p>
    </p>
    <my-color v-model="color1"></my-color>
    <my-color v-model="color2"></my-color>
    <my-color></my-color>
</template>

